                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Hurriyat gags anti-talks group
          MUZAFFAR RAINA                               
	Srinagar, Nov. 23: Hurriyat doves today suspended all posts and issued gag orders on members to silence the growing opposition within the separatist alliance to planned talks with the Centre.        
	It was decided that all posts of the conglomerate stand suspended till further orders. Hurriyat chairman (Mirwaiz (Umar Faoooq) will be restructuring the Hurriyat at the earliest, a spokesperson said after a meeting of the executive council, its top decision-making body.        
	Sources said the meeting was concerned over statements by some of the dissidents criticising the quiet diplomacy, quiet talks policy  a phrase used by home minister P. Chidambaram for the proposed dialogue  and suggestions that the top leaders retire.         
	It was agreed that statements issued by some members not only violates the (Hurriyat) constitution but also goes against the interest of the conglomerate. The Mirwaiz will direct the general and executive councils not to issue statements individually, the spokesperson said.        
	Provincial president Nayeem Khan has been leading the dissidents. Those tired of the struggle should retire and stay home, Khan had said in a jibe at those who favoured taking part in the talks. Some dissidents had even held a secret meeting to discuss the future course of action.                                                                                                                                                           
